<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="477" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,937,1394]" pageId="16" pageNumber="477">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1045,1070]" pageId="16" pageNumber="477">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Smallest 
<taxonomicName box="[425,488,1046,1069]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Sorex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="16" pageNumber="477" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[425,488,1046,1069]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="477">Sorex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in NCA. Color of dorsum is rusty brown to reddish brown, venter slightly paler. U3 &lt;U4. Pigment of teeth not the usual red color for 
<taxonomicName box="[737,799,1082,1105]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Sorex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="16" pageNumber="477" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[737,799,1082,1105]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="477">Sorex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, instead it is pale light orange to yellowish. Brain case slightly inflated with a short rostrum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="477" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,937,1394]" pageId="16" pageNumber="477">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1153,1178]" pageId="16" pageNumber="477">Description.</emphasis>
Measurements for the 
<typeStatus box="[600,698,1153,1178]" pageId="16" pageNumber="477">holotype</typeStatus>
(and only specimen) of 
<taxonomicName box="[975,1137,1153,1178]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Sorex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="16" pageNumber="477" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="stizodon">
<emphasis box="[975,1137,1153,1178]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="477">Sorex stizodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are: TOT 107; Tail 41, HF 153.5; CBL 17.5, GLS 17.9, LR 5.6, LP 6.0, LUT 2.0, LMT 3.5, CB 8.9, WM2 4.2, 
<collectionCode box="[1096,1144,1190,1213]" country="Liberia" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14548" name="University of Liberia" pageId="16" pageNumber="477">LIB</collectionCode>
, 3.4, DB 5.8, LM 5.8, HC 3.1. Compared to other members of the 
<taxonomicName box="[600,703,1225,1250]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Sorex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="16" pageNumber="477" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="salvini">
<emphasis box="[600,703,1225,1250]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="477">S. salvini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group, 
<taxonomicName box="[790,911,1225,1250]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Sorex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="16" pageNumber="477" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="stizodon">
<emphasis box="[790,911,1225,1250]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="477">S. stizodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is absolutely small in all measurements. It has a relatively inflated cranium relative to cranial length.
</paragraph>
